{
  "text": "Activation with the inflammatory cytokine TNF-\u03b1 leads to microchannel occlusion. Endothelial cell activation with the inflammatory cytokine TNF-\u03b1 is known to upregulate expression of adhesion molecules such as VCAM-1 and ICAM-1 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In pathologic disorders such as sepsis, excessive amounts of cytokines lead to dysregulated adhesion molecule expression in the microvascular endothelium of organs such as the lungs [CITATION_3] . To more appropriately model this process, we cultured HLMVECs in the microfluidic systems for these experiments. Confluent HLMVECs cultured in",
